1. *Ledim* vodu kako bih napravila led. (I'm freezing water to make ice.)
2. Ova hladnoća me *ledi* do kostiju. (This cold is chilling me to the bone.)
3. *Led* je klizav i opasan za hodanje. (Ice is slippery and dangerous to walk on.)
4. Ona *ledi* atmosferu kada uđe u sobu. (She freezes the atmosphere when she enters the room.)
5. *Ledeno* pivo je idealno za vruće letnje dane. (Ice-cold beer is perfect for hot summer days.)
6. Zabrinut sam da će *lediti* noćas, pa sam parkirao auto u garaži. (I'm worried it will freeze tonight, so I parked the car in the garage.)
7. Njegov pogled je *leden* i neugodan. (His gaze is icy and unpleasant.)
8. Sinoć su me *ledile* ruke od hladnoće. (Last night my hands were freezing from the cold.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "ledi" can have different forms depending on the context and the part of speech it represents. In the examples above, we can see the verb form "ledim" (I'm freezing), the present tense verb form "ledi" (he/she/it freezes), the adjective form "ledeno" (ice-cold), the verb form "lediti" (to freeze), the adjective form "leden" (icy), and the verb form "ledile" (were freezing).